                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d381">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94 Commission/587: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Geneva (<persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_VSRG1"
                            type="from">Gilbert</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-12-01T15:00:00+01:00"
                            >December 1, 1932—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 1—1:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>346. Consulate’s 342, November 29, noon.<note n="39" xml:id="d381fn39">Not
                        printed.</note> The Committee of Nineteen met in private and in public
                    session this morning. As anticipated no discussion took place on the substance
                    of the dispute. Consideration was given to a letter from <persName
                        corresp="frus1932v03#p_YWW1">Yen</persName> under date of November 29
                    requesting the Committee to draw up a proposal to be submitted to the Assembly
                    fixing definitely and finally the length of the prolongation of the period
                    prescribed by the Covenant for the completion of the Assembly’s report on the
                    conflict (Consulate’s 214, July 2, 9 p.m. and 277, October 1, 3 p.m.). The
                    Committee agreed that the President should reply to the effect that it was
                    impossible to prepare such a proposal until after the Assembly had discussed the
                    question as a whole and had thus provided the Committee with a basis on which to
                    proceed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_VSRG1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Gilbert</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
